caption: Certainly a spot worth trying, the food is awesome and fresh, the cost is reasonable and it is regularly clean here. Highly recommended.
Delicious sushi and great lunch special!

I can’t say enough glowing things about Kyoto. They have delivered to us at least once a week (more often twice a week) for years. ALWAYS OUTSTANDING. Their prices are extraordinarily fair for what they offer. Their sashimi is always so fresh and perfectly cut.  When Kyoto closed during the pandemic, we tried Hibino, which was OVERLY expensive and…. Just couldn’t hold a candle to how Kyoto sushi chefs slice sashimi. We just stopped eating Japanese - without Kyoto, it just wasn’t worth it. Thankfully, they have reopened.  They continue to deliver their A+ food in the midst of this pandemic. Do what you can to support this amazing establishment in our neighborhood.  Order their top notch food!  To everyone who works at Kyoto - thank you for doing what you do and with such speed, kindness, grace, and excellence.  You are treasured and…. Thank you for making and sharing your delish food.

I always order Avacado Rolls. I’m a very picky person when it comes with my food and only like when it’s “clean”. This is the only place which makes Avacado Rolls without Fish Eggs being inside or anywhere around the avacado roll itself & on top of that it doesn’t taste fishy.. (Except once, hence the reason for 4/5 stars)  *In other places, the avacado rolls would be unappetizing for me and definitely cross contaminates with their equipments. If I wanted fish in my avacado rolls I would order like a salmon roll or something..* This is the spot to go for avacado rolls!! Employees are really polite, super nice and attentive!
